  "prompt": "Is Tufts University a good college (moreover, a good engineering college)?",
  "response": "Tufts University is generally considered a very good college, with strengths in several academic areas:\n\nAcademics:\n- Ranked #29 in National Universities by U.S. News & World Report (2022)\n- Highly selective with an acceptance rate around 11-15%\n- Strong liberal arts and research programs\n\nEngineering Specifically:\n- School of Engineering is well-regarded\n- Offers multiple engineering disciplines (Mechanical, Electrical, Computer, Civil, etc.)\n- Ranked #50-60 among engineering schools nationally\n- Known for innovative research and hands-on learning opportunities\n- Offers dual degree programs and interdisciplinary studies\n\nPros:\n- Small class sizes\n- Research opportunities\n- Strong faculty\n- Proximity to Boston (great tech/engineering ecosystem)\n- Good internship and job placement rates\n\nCons:\n- More expensive than some public universities\n- Slightly lower engineering ranking compared to top-tier tech schools\n- Competitive admission process\n\nOverall, Tufts is a solid choice for engineering, especially for students seeking a comprehensive education with strong research opportunities and a collaborative environment. However, top-tier engineering students might also consider schools like MIT, Stanford, or Cal Poly.",
